       _R_G_B stands for red, green, and blue.  This  program  visually  combines
       three raster map layers to form a color image. For each layer, the cor-
       responding component from the layer's color table is used (e.g. for the
       red  layer, the red component is used, and so on). In general, the lay-
       ers should use a grey-scale color table.

